cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on vehicle re-identification using surveillance video analysis, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel model that leverages discriminative feature and dictionary learning, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper introduces external memory modules to emphasize the consistency of each part, which involves memory networks and could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper addresses the challenge of intra-class differences in local regions of the vehicle, which could be related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
